ENTRY       EC 3.1.22.5                 Enzyme
NAME        deoxyribonuclease X;
            Escherichia coli endodeoxyribonuclease;
            Escherichia coli endodeoxyribonuclease X
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on ester bonds;
            Endodeoxyribonucleases producing 3'-phosphomonoesters
REACTION    Endonucleolytic cleavage of supercoiled plasma DNA to linear DNA duplexes
COMMENT     Preference for supercoiled DNA; little activity on linear double-stranded DNA. Inhibited by single-stranded DNA, ATP and AMP.
HISTORY     EC 3.1.22.5 created 1992
REFERENCE   1
  AUTHORS   Ghosh, S. and DasGupta, U.
  TITLE     Studies with endonuclease X: a new deoxyendonuclease of E. coli that preferentially cleaves supercoiled plasmid DNA.
  JOURNAL   Curr. Trends Life Sci. 12 (1984) 79-88.
